{"by":"madaxe_again","id":47775163,"kids":[47776714,47775256],"parent":47774789,"text":"E16 was the hook that caught me and landed me, flopping and writhing, on the decks of Linux - I saw a black and white printout of someone’s desktop, and immediately set about figuring out how to get this unbelievable coolness working on my laptop. By the time I was done I was muttering modelines in my sleep, and had already committed my first patches to a kernel module.<p>I wonder how many other teenagers got catfished into becoming software devs and sysadmins by the siren song of rasterman.","time":1776232259,"type":"comment"}